<dl id="un4045ck"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="un4" href="#un4045">UN4: </a>  <a href="../../FF/unbs/un4all.htm#un4045ck"> (NLI.5A) 45(ck)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> still in body <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="un4045ck"><li>Ulysses </li><li><a href="../../ulex/n/lexn.htm#un4045ck">2021</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/n/n86.htm#un4045ck">2017</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/n/n86.htm#un4045ck">1986 (12.362)</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/n/l22n.htm#un4045ck">1922</a> </li><li><ms href="#un4045ck">MS PL-1</ms> </li><li>JJA 19:108 </li><li><a name="nd6" href="../udra/u12da.htm#nd6">Usage</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/n/nd6.htm#un4045ck">Draft: 12.6</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">If this be so&mdash;says the present President of the Society for Psychical Research, Mrs. Sidgwick&mdash;the question what mind this is becomes of extreme interest. Can it be a mind <mark>still in the body</mark>? or have we got relation with minds which have survived bodily death and are endeavouring by means of cross-correspondences to produce evidence of their operation? <small> Oliver Lodge, <a name="OLSM" href="/udra/udex.htm#OLSM"><cite title="source">The Survival of Man</cite></a> (1920), 337</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
